intentionally repeat any entries. Let’s get this right for the user without clutter or confusion!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No concrete extra setup is needed. The artifact already brings its required runtime dependencies transitively, including Netty common and Bouncy Castle, and normal usage is in-process X.509/CRL test certificate generation without Docker services or required environment/system properties.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment variables or system properties are required. Tests should use normal in-process CertificateBuilder/X509Bundle flows. Be careful with ML-DSA/ML-KEM coverage: those paths are JDK-version-sensitive, so prefer real JDK-supported key generation on JDK 24+ or guard assumptions instead of relying on fake ML-DSA PublicKey stubs.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The reported failure is in the ML-DSA reflective path for java.security.AsymmetricKey/native-image reachability, not evidence of a missing Maven dependency, Docker service, or environment property.\",\n    \"Broadly parameterizing all CertificateBuilder.Algorithm values can hit unsupported or very slow algorithms such as large RSA sizes; tests should check algorithm support as upstream tests do.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0eb76189f4aec2ef016a3eae1033d481969729808a5333076e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1131, "output": 1279, "cacheRead": 28160, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30570, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782492668451, "responseId": "resp_0eb76189f4aec2ef016a3eadfd021c8196890eadc7d17e638e"}}
